01:52:02,250 --> 01:52:03,585
Go ahead.

2047
01:52:03,618 --> 01:52:05,954
Mr. President, I just
talked with Honolulu.

2048
01:52:05,988 --> 01:52:10,192
All the primaries were hit,
and no ships were struck.

2049
01:52:10,225 --> 01:52:14,562
Now, we did lose two aircraft to antiair.

2050
01:52:14,596 --> 01:52:15,697
No Russian ships?

2051
01:52:15,730 --> 01:52:17,765
We didn't hit any Russian ships?

2052
01:52:17,799 --> 01:52:21,736
No, but as I say, two pilots are down.

2053
01:52:21,769 --> 01:52:24,472
I won't know about civilian
causalities until we have the photos.

2054
01:52:24,506 --> 01:52:27,875
Now, if the weather holds,
we can send the RFs in

2055
01:52:27,909 --> 01:52:29,387
to see just what collateral damage...

2056
01:52:29,411 --> 01:52:31,079
All right, Bob.
Thank you.

2057
01:52:31,113 --> 01:52:33,281
Thank you.

2058
01:52:36,351 --> 01:52:39,021
Man, on TV: Pentagon sources tell "CBS News"

2059
01:52:39,054 --> 01:52:40,788
that General Westmoreland has been granted

2060
01:52:40,822 --> 01:52:43,591
even great authority
over the use of B-52s

2061
01:52:43,625 --> 01:52:46,694
in Vietcong-controlled areas
in the south.

2062
01:52:46,728 --> 01:52:49,831
With the recent escalation of
bombing over North Vietnam

2063
01:52:49,864 --> 01:52:52,100
aimed at destroying the heart of the enemy's

2064
01:52:52,134 --> 01:52:54,436
urban industrial capacity,

2065
01:52:54,469 --> 01:52:56,338
the U.S. clearly wants
to force a change

2066
01:52:56,371 --> 01:52:58,906
in Hanoi's will to continue the war.

2067
01:52:58,940 --> 01:53:01,976
Last year, the rate of
Rolling Thunder missions flown

2068
01:53:02,010 --> 01:53:04,679
reached 1,500 per week.

2069
01:53:04,712 --> 01:53:06,981
Since then the rate of sorties has doubled.

2070
01:53:07,015 --> 01:53:10,018
Mr. President, it appears
that the air strikes

2071
01:53:10,052 --> 01:53:14,056
have had no effect on the
enemy's war-making capability.

2072
01:53:14,089 --> 01:53:16,058
The attacks were not successful?

2073
01:53:16,091 --> 01:53:18,826
Well, while we did destroy nearly 100%

2074
01:53:18,860 --> 01:53:20,795
of their oil storage capacity

2075
01:53:20,828 --> 01:53:24,299
in our follow-up attacks
throughout the summer,

2076
01:53:24,332 --> 01:53:26,801
a large portion of their
stock was put into barrels

2077
01:53:26,834 --> 01:53:29,437
and dispersed in anticipation
of our strikes.

2078
01:53:29,471 --> 01:53:32,040
They've retained enough to
meet ongoing requirements.

2079
01:53:32,074 --> 01:53:34,042
Their buildup is continuing.

2080
01:53:34,076 --> 01:53:37,179
And Westmoreland is
requesting additional men.

2081
01:53:37,212 --> 01:53:38,880
How many?

2082
01:53:38,913 --> 01:53:40,982
The Program Three forces will bring us up

2083
01:53:41,015 --> 01:53:44,652
to 431,000 by the middle of '67.

2084
01:53:46,121 --> 01:53:47,522
What about the bombing?

2085
01:53:47,555 --> 01:53:51,359
We're looking at heavier B-52
strikes in the southern DMZ,

2086
01:53:51,393 --> 01:53:55,397
and in North Vietnam,
targets in the restricted zones.

2087
01:53:55,430 --> 01:53:56,898
Downtown Hanoi.

2088
01:53:56,931 --> 01:53:58,500
Yes, sir, and Haiphong,

2089
01:53:58,533 --> 01:54:00,668
and in the buffer zone with China.

2090
01:54:00,702 --> 01:54:02,036
The good news,
Mr. President,

2091
01:54:02,070 --> 01:54:03,314
is that the naysayers were wrong.

2092
01:54:03,338 --> 01:54:05,773
Peking and Moscow stood still,

2093
01:54:05,807 --> 01:54:07,609
and they will very likely stand still

2094
01:54:07,642 --> 01:54:09,644
even with intensified activity.

2095
01:54:13,448 --> 01:54:16,451
Are you recommending some of
these new targets for me today?

2096
01:54:16,484 --> 01:54:19,954
Yes, I am. You have the
evaluation sheets before you.

2097
01:54:19,987 --> 01:54:21,789
I have some photographs here.

2098
01:54:21,823 --> 01:54:25,260
The Van Dien truck depot.

2099
01:54:25,293 --> 01:54:28,230
That the one with the school up the street?

2100
01:54:32,800 --> 01:54:36,538
As a matter of fact, yes,
the Polish Friendship School

2101
01:54:36,571 --> 01:54:38,740
across the highway, a half a mile up.

2102
01:54:38,773 --> 01:54:41,276
Mr. President,
as you may recall,

2103
01:54:41,309 --> 01:54:42,944
in order to avoid a tax increase,

2104
01:54:42,977 --> 01:54:46,214
we did not budget for the war
beyond this fiscal year,

2105
01:54:46,248 --> 01:54:48,750
which has cost us 20 billion

2106
01:54:48,783 --> 01:54:51,686
as opposed to the 12 billion projected.

2107
01:54:54,322 --> 01:54:57,825
We are over by eight billion?

2108
01:54:57,859 --> 01:54:59,594
Eight billion?

2109
01:55:02,430 --> 01:55:06,701
Mr. President, if you
approve these new forces,

2110
01:55:06,734 --> 01:55:09,137
constraints on domestic programs

2111
01:55:09,171 --> 01:55:12,106
will no longer be avoidable.

2112
01:55:12,140 --> 01:55:14,542
It's all in a memo I sent over to you today

2113
01:55:14,576 --> 01:55:17,379
along with some recommendations.

2114
01:55:24,619 --> 01:55:25,787
Joe.

2115
01:55:25,820 --> 01:55:29,691
I want to start working on
the State of the Union.

2116
01:55:32,960 --> 01:55:35,663
You sit down with Bob and Walt and Fowler.

2117
01:55:35,697 --> 01:55:37,832
Yes, Mr. President.

2118
01:55:42,069 --> 01:55:44,172
There's to be no mention
of the Great Society!

2119
01:55:59,754 --> 01:56:01,423
What is it you're looking for?

2120
01:56:01,456 --> 01:56:03,358
Undersecretary of state?

2121
01:56:03,391 --> 01:56:06,928
I'll change the title to the
Holy Roman Emperor, right?

2122
01:56:06,961 --> 01:56:12,200
No, this is the best way
I can serve your presidency.

2123
01:56:12,234 --> 01:56:16,571
And I think Dean Rusk would feel undercut

2124
01:56:16,604 --> 01:56:19,207
if you were to fill George Ball's job

2125
01:56:19,241 --> 01:56:21,643
with a personal friend of yours.

2126
01:56:21,676 --> 01:56:23,578
I don't give a rat's ass what Rusk feels!

2127
01:56:23,611 --> 01:56:25,780
I need you in that room, Clark.

2128
01:56:25,813 --> 01:56:28,716
I need someone like George with
an ability to reason and argue.

2129
01:56:28,750 --> 01:56:30,084
A devil's advocate.

2130
01:56:30,117 --> 01:56:34,088
George Ball was not
playing devil's advocate.

2131
01:56:34,121 --> 01:56:37,325
He believes every word he says.

2132
01:56:39,160 --> 01:56:40,995
All right.

2133
01:56:41,028 --> 01:56:42,430
All right.

2134
01:56:46,968 --> 01:56:48,936
Moyers wants the job.

2135
01:56:48,970 --> 01:56:52,106
My press man thinks if I make
him number two at State,

2136
01:56:52,139 --> 01:56:54,942
I'll all of a sudden give a shit
what he thinks about Vietnam.

2137
01:56:56,110 --> 01:56:59,113
And McNamara.
McNamara sends me a paper.

2138
01:56:59,146 --> 01:57:01,583
Says we should cap the troops,
level off the bombing.

2139
01:57:01,616 --> 01:57:03,518
You know what happens if I stop bombing?

2140
01:57:03,551 --> 01:57:06,621
Ho Chi Minh runs five
more divisions up my ass,

2141
01:57:06,654 --> 01:57:09,324
that's what happens!

2142
01:57:09,357 --> 01:57:12,193
It was McNamara's program, the whole thing.

2143
01:57:12,226 --> 01:57:14,362
Now he's talking up a shitstorm with Bobby.

2144
01:57:14,396 --> 01:57:15,363
You don't know that.

2145
01:57:15,397 --> 01:57:17,299
I know everything.

2146
01:57:17,332 --> 01:57:20,468
I know who's saying what at those
fancy Georgetown dinner parties.

2147
01:57:20,502 --> 01:57:23,271
I know 'cause I had Hoover put
a couple of boys there, too.

2148
01:57:23,305 --> 01:57:24,406
I know.

2149
01:57:24,439 --> 01:57:26,974
What they say doesn't matter.

2150
01:57:27,008 --> 01:57:29,611
You're not helpless in this situation.

2151
01:57:29,644 --> 01:57:31,446
Your approval ratings are down.

2152
01:57:31,479 --> 01:57:36,318
You need to go out there on
the stump and sell the truth.

2153
01:57:36,351 --> 01:57:38,219
Westmoreland is now saying

2154
01:57:38,252 --> 01:57:42,624
that a Communist military
victory is impossible.

2155
01:57:42,657 --> 01:57:45,593
You're finally winning in Vietnam.

2156
01:57:45,627 --> 01:57:47,429
We're winning, but we're losing.

2157
01:57:47,462 --> 01:57:49,631
We're killing 'em, and we're losing.

2158
01:57:49,664 --> 01:57:54,268
We're losing because this war
goes on and on and on!

2159
01:57:54,302 --> 01:57:55,937
I passed twice the number of bills.

2160
01:57:55,970 --> 01:57:57,905
FDR got through in his first hundred days.

2161
01:57:57,939 --> 01:58:00,708
200 in the last two years!

2162
01:58:00,742 --> 01:58:03,545
There's never been an era in
American history like this,

2163
01:58:03,578 --> 01:58:06,848
yet there's so much left to do.

2164
01:58:06,881 --> 01:58:11,386
But this war has got to end!

2165
01:58:11,419 --> 01:58:14,922
Five years pussyfooting about in
that miserable little country.

2166
01:58:14,956 --> 01:58:17,359
$2 billion a month!

2167
01:58:17,392 --> 01:58:20,395
We could be feeding these
people, educating these people!

2168
01:58:20,428 --> 01:58:23,565
God damn it! Why won't that son
of a bitch let me help him?

2169
01:58:23,598 --> 01:58:25,132
Why?

2170
01:58:25,166 --> 01:58:26,601
Why won't he lay down his arms

2171
01:58:26,634 --> 01:58:31,739
and stop killing off his sons
in the flower of their youth?

2172
01:58:31,773 --> 01:58:33,941
I do not understand.

2173
01:58:33,975 --> 01:58:36,878
I just do not understand.

2174
01:58:40,448 --> 01:58:43,918
Mr. President...

2175
01:58:43,951 --> 01:58:46,354
Moyers.
Get me Moyers.

2176
01:58:46,388 --> 01:58:49,457
And get me General Westmoreland
on the other line.

2177
01:58:49,491 --> 01:58:50,792
Can I help you,
Mr. President?

2178
01:58:50,825 --> 01:58:53,595
Get your bags packed.

2179
01:58:55,430 --> 01:58:59,634
Call the press together.
We're going to Vietnam.

2180
01:59:12,279 --> 01:59:14,348
Dean?

2181
01:59:17,919 --> 01:59:19,587
Are they ours?

2182
01:59:19,621 --> 01:59:21,188
I fucking hope so.

2183
02:00:03,164 --> 02:00:06,333
Present arms!

2184
02:00:08,803 --> 02:00:11,939
Order... hut!

2185
02:01:03,758 --> 02:01:05,226
Where you from, son?

2186
02:01:05,259 --> 02:01:06,427
Louisville, Kentucky, sir.

2187
02:01:06,460 --> 02:01:08,496
- Kentucky?
- Yes, sir.

2188
02:01:08,530 --> 02:01:10,273
Have you reached majority age yet, Corporal?

2189
02:01:10,297 --> 02:01:12,767
I was 21 last month, sir.

2190
02:01:12,800 --> 02:01:15,913
My mom and my girl sent me a big old chocolate
cake, and it came just in time, sir.

2191
02:01:15,937 --> 02:01:19,240
- Good. Bill, get 'em out.
- Yes, Mr. President.

2192
02:01:19,273 --> 02:01:22,677
Well, they've given me
the honor, Corporal McCaffrey,

2193
02:01:22,710 --> 02:01:26,581
of pinning you with this Purple Heart here.

2194
02:01:26,614 --> 02:01:27,882
There.

2195
02:01:27,915 --> 02:01:29,350
You'll be home right soon,

2196
02:01:29,383 --> 02:01:30,628
and on the first Tuesday of November,

2197
02:01:30,652 --> 02:01:32,353
you got a congressional election.

2198
02:01:32,386 --> 02:01:34,622
I want you to vote.

2199
02:01:34,656 --> 02:01:36,290
Yes, sir.

2200
02:01:36,323 --> 02:01:39,160
You'll be able to get to your polling place?

2201
02:01:39,193 --> 02:01:41,195
I don't know where it is,
but I'll get a ride, sir.

2202
02:01:41,228 --> 02:01:43,598
All right.

2203
02:01:46,033 --> 02:01:47,101
Make sure you vote now.

2204
02:01:47,134 --> 02:01:49,003
Yes, sir.

2205
02:01:51,138 --> 02:01:53,875
We're all behind you, sir.

2206
02:01:53,908 --> 02:01:56,811
Every one of us.

2207
02:01:56,844 --> 02:02:00,214
We won't let you down.

2208
02:02:00,247 --> 02:02:01,215
All right, son.

2209
02:02:01,248 --> 02:02:04,351
Thank you.

2210
02:02:04,385 --> 02:02:06,621
And I won't let you down!

2211
02:02:06,654 --> 02:02:09,557
You'll get everything you need.

2212
02:02:09,591 --> 02:02:12,860
I thank you.
I salute you.

2213
02:02:12,894 --> 02:02:15,597
May the good Lord look
over you and keep you safe

2214
02:02:15,630 --> 02:02:18,700
until you come home and nail
that coonskin to the wall.

2215
02:02:18,733 --> 02:02:21,836
Three cheers for the
president! Hip hip...

2216
02:02:21,869 --> 02:02:23,237
Hooray!

2217
02:02:23,270 --> 02:02:24,238
- Hip hip...
- Hooray!

2218
02:02:24,271 --> 02:02:26,507
- Hip hip...
- Hooray!

2219
02:03:21,863 --> 02:03:24,231
Certainly the bombing of the north

2220
02:03:24,265 --> 02:03:26,701
makes the war more costly and more difficult

2221
02:03:26,734 --> 02:03:29,971
and more painful for North Vietnam.

2222
02:03:30,004 --> 02:03:32,606
It is a harsh punishment indeed.

2223
02:03:32,640 --> 02:03:35,476
But we are not in Vietnam to play the part

2224
02:03:35,509 --> 02:03:37,812
of an avenging angel pouring
death and destruction.

2225
02:03:37,845 --> 02:03:42,183
Kennedy, McCarthy

2226
02:03:42,216 --> 02:03:44,852
haven't done a thing for this country!

2227
02:03:44,886 --> 02:03:47,254
Not a fucking thing!

2228
02:03:47,288 --> 02:03:49,590
And look at all I've done!

2229
02:03:49,623 --> 02:03:51,534
It should be clear by now that
the bombing of the north

2230
02:03:51,558 --> 02:03:54,862
cannot bring an end to the war in the south

2231
02:03:54,896 --> 02:03:56,563
and that indeed at the present time

2232
02:03:56,597 --> 02:03:59,200
it may well be prolonging that war.

2233
02:03:59,233 --> 02:04:00,702
Our troops are being killed

2234
02:04:00,735 --> 02:04:03,537
by the bullets and the mines of the south.

2235
02:04:03,570 --> 02:04:05,406
If by ending the bombing of the north,

2236
02:04:05,439 --> 02:04:08,075
we can bring peace to South Vietnam,

2237
02:04:08,109 --> 02:04:10,244
we will save the lives of thousands of...

2238
02:04:10,277 --> 02:04:12,279
I don't know why you're
worried about Kennedy

2239
02:04:12,313 --> 02:04:14,949
and your second term.

2240
02:04:14,982 --> 02:04:16,383
Because I don't think your health

2241
02:04:16,417 --> 02:04:19,353
will survive your first term.

2242
02:04:19,386 --> 02:04:21,455
Where you going?

2243
02:04:21,488 --> 02:04:23,190
I want to be useful to you.

2244
02:04:23,224 --> 02:04:25,359
And I would listen even
as you rant and rave,

2245
02:04:25,392 --> 02:04:27,028
but I have worked far too hard

2246
02:04:27,061 --> 02:04:30,865
and borne far too much to
watch you destroy yourself.

2247
02:04:37,171 --> 02:04:39,974
Major political elements of South Vietnam

2248
02:04:40,007 --> 02:04:42,977
to participate in their
choice of leadership...

2249
02:04:46,047 --> 02:04:49,150
The bridge is a major target,
and we've never hit it.

2250
02:04:49,183 --> 02:04:51,685
The chance of civilian deaths
will be almost zero.

2251
02:04:51,719 --> 02:04:54,288
I say 100 to 500, possibly more.

2252
02:04:54,321 --> 02:04:55,990
Which is it, 500 or zero?

2253
02:04:56,023 --> 02:04:58,559
Mr. President, the Stennis
Committee is up in arms

2254
02:04:58,592 --> 02:05:00,627
over our holding back on these targets.

2255
02:05:00,661 --> 02:05:02,263
Bob's testimony is coming up,

2256
02:05:02,296 --> 02:05:03,831
and it might take some heat off him

2257
02:05:03,865 --> 02:05:06,300
if some of these can be cleared
up before his appearance.

2258
02:05:06,333 --> 02:05:08,535
I can take the heat
without padding my resume

2259
02:05:08,569 --> 02:05:09,804
with more bombing missions.

2260
02:05:09,837 --> 02:05:11,148
This is a heavily defended target

2261
02:05:11,172 --> 02:05:12,940
in a very populated area.

2262
02:05:12,974 --> 02:05:14,842
The photos are right here,
Mr. President.

2263
02:05:14,876 --> 02:05:16,010
The photos are meaningless.

2264
02:05:16,043 --> 02:05:17,745
The target is heavily defended.

2265
02:05:17,779 --> 02:05:19,046
The pilots jettison their bombs

2266
02:05:19,080 --> 02:05:20,281
when they're under attack.

2267
02:05:20,314 --> 02:05:21,816
Now, I've been asking for two years

2268
02:05:21,849 --> 02:05:23,360
why they don't come straight up the river.

2269
02:05:23,384 --> 02:05:24,661
That way, if they dump the bombs,

2270
02:05:24,685 --> 02:05:26,163
they go in the water and not on the people,

2271
02:05:26,187 --> 02:05:27,364
and I still haven't got an answer.

2272
02:05:27,388 --> 02:05:30,157
Coming in from the gulf involves
an extra turn,

2273
02:05:30,191 --> 02:05:32,359
with our backs to those heavy defenses.

