without my permission.

2322
02:09:25,826 --> 02:09:27,761
I'll have the commanders
go down the line again.

2323
02:09:27,794 --> 02:09:29,630
Not one bullet, damn it!

2324
02:09:58,692 --> 02:10:01,428
Get off me!
Let me go!

2325
02:10:01,462 --> 02:10:04,598
Let me go!
Just let me go!

2326
02:10:06,967 --> 02:10:09,336
Look at that.

2327
02:10:12,473 --> 02:10:15,342
There he is!
There's McNamara!

2328
02:10:15,376 --> 02:10:17,544
There's McNamara!

2329
02:10:33,327 --> 02:10:36,297
Secretary McNamara, on behalf
of the subcommittee,

2330
02:10:36,330 --> 02:10:39,600
let me thank you for your
appearance here today.

2331
02:10:39,633 --> 02:10:44,338
I have, from the beginning, and do today,

2332
02:10:44,371 --> 02:10:48,742
fully support the objectives of the bombing

2333
02:10:48,775 --> 02:10:51,178
to interdict men and supplies

2334
02:10:51,212 --> 02:10:54,181
and hinder the enemy's ability
to wage war in the south.

2335
02:10:54,215 --> 02:10:58,852
In this I am 100% behind the joint chiefs,

2336
02:10:58,885 --> 02:11:00,421
Admiral Sharp,

2337
02:11:00,454 --> 02:11:03,357
General Westmoreland and his commanders,

2338
02:11:03,390 --> 02:11:05,659
as they are fully aware

2339
02:11:05,692 --> 02:11:07,894
and as the president is aware.

2340
02:11:07,928 --> 02:11:11,732
We are all greatly encouraged
to hear that, Mr. Secretary.

2341
02:11:11,765 --> 02:11:15,202
You are the last to testify, as you know,

2342
02:11:15,236 --> 02:11:18,205
and the overwhelming view

2343
02:11:18,239 --> 02:11:19,840
from General Wheeler and the others

2344
02:11:19,873 --> 02:11:23,344
is that there has been excessive
interference from your office...

2345
02:11:23,377 --> 02:11:26,480
If I'd be permitted to finish
my statement, Senator Stennis.

2346
02:11:26,513 --> 02:11:29,850
There are copies available
outside the hearing room.

2347
02:11:29,883 --> 02:11:34,121
Our greater objective, however,
was, and remains,

2348
02:11:34,155 --> 02:11:36,323
to persuade the leaders of North Vietnam

2349
02:11:36,357 --> 02:11:38,992
that they cannot prevail.

2350
02:11:39,025 --> 02:11:42,196
In this we have been unsuccessful.

2351
02:11:42,229 --> 02:11:44,565
This is due to the fact that North Vietnam

2352
02:11:44,598 --> 02:11:46,900
can sustain its forces in the south

2353
02:11:46,933 --> 02:11:49,903
with a mere 100 tons of supplies a day,

2354
02:11:49,936 --> 02:11:52,005
85 of which they can acquire

2355
02:11:52,038 --> 02:11:55,809
through corrupt elements in the
South Vietnamese government.

2356
02:11:55,842 --> 02:11:59,079
Out of 359 targets
recommended by the chiefs,

2357
02:11:59,112 --> 02:12:01,215
only 57 remain unstruck.

2358
02:12:01,248 --> 02:12:03,617
Two are battery plants

2359
02:12:03,650 --> 02:12:06,753
manufacturing a total of 600 tons a year,

2360
02:12:06,787 --> 02:12:10,090
not enough to fill the corner of a
Sears-Roebuck regional warehouse.

2361
02:12:10,123 --> 02:12:11,758
Just a moment,
Mr. Secretary.

2362
02:12:11,792 --> 02:12:14,628
There's a rubber plant
producing 30 tires a day.

2363
02:12:14,661 --> 02:12:17,030
The service station where I fill my car

2364
02:12:17,063 --> 02:12:18,675
could supply the output of this facility.

2365
02:12:18,699 --> 02:12:22,669
Hitting these targets
will cost us in pilots,

2366
02:12:22,703 --> 02:12:25,406
planes and hard cash,

2367
02:12:25,439 --> 02:12:29,443
and they will kill more and more civilians.

2368
02:12:29,476 --> 02:12:32,179
The military knows this.

2369
02:12:32,213 --> 02:12:34,648
They think it's worth it.

2370
02:12:34,681 --> 02:12:36,317
I do not.

2371
02:12:37,884 --> 02:12:39,320
Order!

2372
02:12:39,353 --> 02:12:41,054
You know what he did to me out there?

2373
02:12:41,087 --> 02:12:42,323
It's like selling your house

2374
02:12:42,356 --> 02:12:44,057
and your son takes the buyer aside

2375
02:12:44,090 --> 02:12:46,693
and tells him there's leaks in the basement.

2376
02:12:46,727 --> 02:12:49,996
Now Hanoi knows we're divided,
and they'll never stop.

2377
02:12:50,030 --> 02:12:51,765
I've gotta get rid of that son of a bitch.

2378
02:12:51,798 --> 02:12:54,601
You can't just get rid of him.

2379
02:12:54,635 --> 02:12:56,437
The Republicans will play up the disunity.

2380
02:12:56,470 --> 02:12:58,004
Bobby will have a field day.

2381
02:12:58,038 --> 02:13:00,207
Bobby's clamoring for him to
resign, don't you know,

2382
02:13:00,241 --> 02:13:03,477
to go public against me
for doing what he advised!

2383
02:13:03,510 --> 02:13:06,313
Look, we'll find a job for McNamara

2384
02:13:06,347 --> 02:13:08,114
where he won't be able to snipe at you.

2385
02:13:08,148 --> 02:13:10,817
I'll help you fill his post
with someone you can trust.

2386
02:13:10,851 --> 02:13:13,454
I'll do anything I can
for you, Mr. President.

2387
02:13:13,487 --> 02:13:16,122
But we have a reelection campaign to start,

2388
02:13:16,156 --> 02:13:18,992
and you do not have a policy
to end this war.

2389
02:13:21,428 --> 02:13:25,999
Clark, you'll do anything you can?

2390
02:13:34,308 --> 02:13:36,076
They're ready for you,
Mr. President.

2391
02:13:36,109 --> 02:13:39,079
Yeah. I'll be out
in a minute.

2392
02:13:39,112 --> 02:13:40,814
Sit down, Bob.

2393
02:13:46,487 --> 02:13:49,122
I'm sorry you found out
from the "Washington Post."

2394
02:13:49,155 --> 02:13:52,626
I'm sure Fowler told you,
or the bank people.

2395
02:13:52,659 --> 02:13:54,728
Nobody told me anything,
Mr. President.

2396
02:13:54,761 --> 02:13:57,464
I, mentioned to you in the spring

2397
02:13:57,498 --> 02:13:58,908
that I'd been approached by the World Bank,

2398
02:13:58,932 --> 02:14:01,835
but I thought if you were
going to nominate me,

2399
02:14:01,868 --> 02:14:04,237
you would have said something yourself.

2400
02:14:04,271 --> 02:14:07,173
Doing fine work there.
Humanitarian work.

2401
02:14:07,207 --> 02:14:08,485
I know that's of interest to you.

2402
02:14:08,509 --> 02:14:11,412
Yes, but only if it's what you want.

2403
02:14:11,445 --> 02:14:13,780
If I can no longer be of service...

2404
02:14:13,814 --> 02:14:15,549
Service?

2405
02:14:15,582 --> 02:14:18,452
Who's been of more service to me than you?

2406
02:14:18,485 --> 02:14:21,455
Why, you've served longer than any
defense secretary in history.

2407
02:14:21,488 --> 02:14:23,624
Look what you've had to shepherd us through.

2408
02:14:23,657 --> 02:14:26,360
The Cuban crisis...
Two Cuban crisises,

2409
02:14:26,393 --> 02:14:28,762
Berlin, Dominican, Middle East.

2410
02:14:28,795 --> 02:14:32,132
Hell, that's a tough
enough job in peacetime.

2411
02:14:32,165 --> 02:14:34,935
And look what you've had to deal with.

2412
02:14:34,968 --> 02:14:37,504
Mr. President,

2413
02:14:37,538 --> 02:14:39,640
the point is...

2414
02:14:39,673 --> 02:14:44,778
I don't have to leave
until you want me to leave.

2415
02:14:44,811 --> 02:14:46,647
Bob,

2416
02:14:46,680 --> 02:14:49,149
Joe Fowler asked me for three nominees.

2417
02:14:49,182 --> 02:14:51,952
McNamara.

2418
02:14:51,985 --> 02:14:54,955
There were tears in the
treasury secretary's eyes

2419
02:14:54,988 --> 02:14:57,157
'cause he was hoping he'd be my choice.

2420
02:14:57,190 --> 02:14:59,259
And with tears in his eyes,

2421
02:14:59,292 --> 02:15:01,795
he said he had to submit
three names to the bank.

2422
02:15:01,828 --> 02:15:05,832
I said, "Okay. McNamara,
McNamara, and McNamara."

2423
02:15:05,866 --> 02:15:07,300
You ask him.

2424
02:15:07,334 --> 02:15:10,637
Now, the bank directors vote today,

2425
02:15:10,671 --> 02:15:13,774
but it's, it's just a formality.

2426
02:15:13,807 --> 02:15:16,443
Now, Bob, I better get over

2427
02:15:16,477 --> 02:15:18,945
to Lady Bird's beautification awards.

2428
02:15:18,979 --> 02:15:20,514
It's important to her.

2429
02:15:20,547 --> 02:15:23,684
Your wife's the same with her
reading program, I know.

2430
02:15:23,717 --> 02:15:26,820
Yes, although with her condition,

2431
02:15:26,853 --> 02:15:28,021
it's been difficult.

2432
02:15:28,054 --> 02:15:31,091
No improvement since surgery?

2433
02:15:31,124 --> 02:15:35,261
My son...

2434
02:15:35,295 --> 02:15:37,297
he has them as well.

2435
02:15:38,932 --> 02:15:41,101
You deserve whatever you want
from this government.

2436
02:15:41,134 --> 02:15:43,770
My obligation is to help you,

2437
02:15:43,804 --> 02:15:46,006
and this was within my power to grant you.

2438
02:15:49,376 --> 02:15:54,047
People have an obligation to the president,

2439
02:15:54,080 --> 02:15:56,216
not the other way around.

2440
02:16:02,489 --> 02:16:06,159
"May your selfless service,
spent in defending freedom,

2441
02:16:06,192 --> 02:16:08,361
"bring even greater rewards

2442
02:16:08,395 --> 02:16:10,263
"in the larger work that you now undertake

2443
02:16:10,296 --> 02:16:12,165
to promote freedom throughout
the world."

2444
02:16:12,198 --> 02:16:15,936
Signed, Lyndon B. Johnson,
President.

2445
02:16:20,974 --> 02:16:23,844
This is the Medal of Freedom,

2446
02:16:23,877 --> 02:16:26,747
the highest award a president can bestow

2447
02:16:26,780 --> 02:16:30,383
upon a citizen of the United States.

2448
02:16:30,417 --> 02:16:35,055
I award it now to a loyal,
brilliant, good man.

2449
02:16:35,088 --> 02:16:38,592
Robert McNamara, the very best we have.

2450
02:16:41,895 --> 02:16:43,263
Thank you, Mr. President.

2451
02:16:43,296 --> 02:16:45,566
This is an almost impossible
situation to respond to.

2452
02:16:45,599 --> 02:16:47,200
You're used to impossible situations.

2453
02:17:22,569 --> 02:17:23,570
Thank you.

2454
02:17:33,379 --> 02:17:35,882
Now, I stand here tonight to tell you

2455
02:17:35,916 --> 02:17:39,219
that I regard Bob McNamara here

2456
02:17:39,252 --> 02:17:41,922
as not only one of the smartest,

2457
02:17:41,955 --> 02:17:45,726
but one of the most humane men I know.

2458
02:17:45,759 --> 02:17:47,728
Thank you.

2459
02:17:50,597 --> 02:17:55,101
Put the men in.

2460
02:17:56,603 --> 02:18:00,874
Call up the reserves and
extend tours of duty.

2461
02:18:02,175 --> 02:18:07,047
Expand the bombing.

2462
02:18:18,024 --> 02:18:21,895
Mr. President...

2463
02:18:21,928 --> 02:18:24,665
I cannot...

2464
02:18:26,967 --> 02:18:31,838
find the words to express
what lies in my heart today.

2465
02:18:31,872 --> 02:18:35,642
And...

2466
02:18:35,676 --> 02:18:38,545
I think I better respond at another time.

2467
02:18:39,913 --> 02:18:42,482
Bob.

2468
02:19:01,234 --> 02:19:02,502
One question, please!

2469
02:19:02,535 --> 02:19:04,905
- Over here!
- Mr. Clifford!

2470
02:19:04,938 --> 02:19:06,740
Mr. Clifford,
does your acceptance

2471
02:19:06,773 --> 02:19:08,575
of the job of defense secretary

2472
02:19:08,609 --> 02:19:11,578
signal your interest in elected office?

2473
02:19:11,612 --> 02:19:14,247
It signals only my desire

2474
02:19:14,280 --> 02:19:18,351
to serve a great president
and a longtime friend.

2475
02:19:18,384 --> 02:19:21,254
I am 61 years old,

2476
02:19:21,287 --> 02:19:23,657
and I'm sure this will finish me off.

2477
02:19:26,793 --> 02:19:28,662
John.

2478
02:19:28,695 --> 02:19:31,732
It's been observed that in
your views on Vietnam,

2479
02:19:31,765 --> 02:19:33,600
you've changed from dove to hawk.

2480
02:19:33,634 --> 02:19:34,968
Which are you?

2481
02:19:35,001 --> 02:19:37,671
I am not conscious of falling under

2482
02:19:37,704 --> 02:19:40,573
any of those ornithological divisions.

2483
02:19:40,607 --> 02:19:42,676
I'll tell you this, he's no ostrich.

2484
02:19:44,745 --> 02:19:46,355
I know of no man who will call it as it is

2485
02:19:46,379 --> 02:19:49,650
with such candor and judgment
as this man, Clark Clifford.

2486
02:19:49,683 --> 02:19:51,918
We got a light at the end of the tunnel now!

2487
02:20:01,327 --> 02:20:03,764
It's probably a small attack,
Mr. President.

2488
02:20:03,797 --> 02:20:06,132
The embassy compound's been hit before.

2489
02:20:06,166 --> 02:20:07,801
Mr. Secretary,
it's not just the embassy.

2490
02:20:07,834 --> 02:20:10,236
The palace, legislature, airport, too.

2491
02:20:16,276 --> 02:20:19,179
- Secretary Rusk.
- Put it on the speakerphone.

2492
02:20:21,648 --> 02:20:23,750
Go ahead, Ben.

2493
02:20:23,784 --> 02:20:26,586
Dean, I've got the duty officer
at the embassy, Alan Brandt.

2494
02:20:26,619 --> 02:20:30,456
Mr. Brandt!
Mr. Brandt, can you hear me?

2495
02:20:30,490 --> 02:20:33,193
They're standing right outside,
Mr. Secretary.

2496
02:20:33,226 --> 02:20:34,928
Outside of the embassy compound?

2497
02:20:34,961 --> 02:20:36,329
Inside.

2498
02:20:36,362 --> 02:20:38,498
They blew through the wall.
They're at the door.

2499
02:20:38,531 --> 02:20:40,266
Rostow, casualty report.

2500
02:20:40,300 --> 02:20:43,136
Do you have something to defend
yourself with, Mr. Brandt?

2501
02:20:43,169 --> 02:20:45,338
I'm at the window.
They're below me.

2502
02:20:45,371 --> 02:20:47,640
They see me.
They're looking right at me.

2503
02:20:47,674 --> 02:20:49,109
I've got to go.
Mr. Secretary.

2504
02:20:49,142 --> 02:20:51,044
Small attack?!

2505
02:20:51,077 --> 02:20:53,179
These are desperation moves,
Mr. President.

2506
02:20:53,213 --> 02:20:54,180
We've got them on the run.

2507
02:20:54,214 --> 02:20:56,616
It's not just Saigon.

2508
02:20:58,151 --> 02:21:00,029
Man, on TV: The Vietcong have
launched surprise attacks

2509
02:21:00,053 --> 02:21:03,957
on 36 of the 44 provincial
capitals of South Vietnam.

2510
02:21:03,990 --> 02:21:06,793
From the streets of Hue near the DMZ

2511
02:21:06,827 --> 02:21:09,262
to the U.S. embassy
compound in Saigon,

2512
02:21:09,295 --> 02:21:13,133
the casualty count on both
sides has been unprecedented.

2513
02:21:13,166 --> 02:21:16,069
The U.S. military says
it is successfully

2514
02:21:16,102 --> 02:21:18,271
beating back the Vietcong attacks,

2515
02:21:18,304 --> 02:21:21,107
but clearly they are
paying an enormous price.

2516
02:21:21,141 --> 02:21:24,377
The enemy's well-laid plans
went afoul.

2517
02:21:24,410 --> 02:21:27,280
They tried to ignite a revolution
in the south, and they failed.

2518
02:21:27,313 --> 02:21:30,817
If this is a failure, God help
us when they have a success.

2519
02:21:49,235 --> 02:21:52,138
I've given 'em all the men,
the planes, the guns,

2520
02:21:52,172 --> 02:21:53,706
the bullets he said he needed.

2521
02:21:53,740 --> 02:21:55,541
I thought we were winning this thing!

2522
02:21:55,575 --> 02:21:58,644
Now Westmoreland says he wants
206,000 more troops!

2523
02:21:58,678 --> 02:22:00,713
206,000!

2524
02:22:00,747 --> 02:22:02,883
We'll have 750,000 there.

2525
02:22:02,916 --> 02:22:05,752
Three-quarters of a million men in Vietnam.

2526
02:22:05,786 --> 02:22:07,487
Light at the end of the tunnel.

2527
02:22:07,520 --> 02:22:08,831
Hell, we don't even have a tunnel.

2528
02:22:08,855 --> 02:22:10,656
We don't even know where the tunnel is!

2529
02:22:10,690 --> 02:22:12,325
I want you to get Westmoreland here.

2530
02:22:12,358 --> 02:22:14,427
Get your people together
and look at this thing.

2531
02:22:14,460 --> 02:22:16,062
We'll give 'em the boys if we have to,

2532
02:22:16,096 --> 02:22:17,597
but on your recommendation.

2533
02:22:17,630 --> 02:22:18,698
You'll wait.

2534
02:22:18,731 --> 02:22:20,733
I'll wait, but not for long.

2535
02:22:20,767 --> 02:22:24,404
If he needs 'em, what the hell
am I supposed to do?

2536
02:22:24,437 --> 02:22:28,608
Old friend, get me an answer.

2537
02:22:28,641 --> 02:22:31,845
Give us these troops so we
can seize the initiative!

2538
02:22:31,878 --> 02:22:33,713
But it will just be more of the same!

2539
02:22:33,746 --> 02:22:36,149
The enemy's taken 200,000 killed,

2540
02:22:36,182 --> 02:22:37,717
and he'll take 200,000 more!

2541
02:22:37,750 --> 02:22:39,152
We've lost a tenth that many,

2542
02:22:39,185 --> 02:22:40,854
and Americans are rioting in the streets.

2543
02:22:40,887 --> 02:22:41,955
They should be cheering.

2544
02:22:41,988 --> 02:22:44,825
The Vietcong lost.
We were victorious.

2545
02:22:44,858 --> 02:22:46,326
That's true, Walt, but remember

2546
02:22:46,359 --> 02:22:49,029
they only committed
175,000 men to this offensive,

2547
02:22:49,062 --> 02:22:50,997
holding enough back to strike again.

2548
02:22:51,031 --> 02:22:52,975
That's right, damn it,
and it could happen at any time.

2549
02:22:52,999 --> 02:22:54,467
I say put the men in.

2550
02:22:54,500 --> 02:22:57,270
There are no more trained men.

2551
02:22:57,303 --> 02:22:59,873
We would ship raw troops
and train them in the rear.

2552
02:22:59,906 --> 02:23:03,643
What rear? There is no
rear in Vietnam anymore.

2553
02:23:03,676 --> 02:23:06,679
I would hope we've at least
learned that from this victory.

2554
02:23:06,712 --> 02:23:08,849
With 206,000 more men,

2555
02:23:08,882 --> 02:23:11,317
we could go into Laos,
Cambodia, North Vietnam

2556
02:23:11,351 --> 02:23:13,786
and cut out their supply
routes once and for all.

2557
02:23:13,820 --> 02:23:16,522
We have never been given that authority!

2558
02:23:16,556 --> 02:23:18,324
Excuse me, General.

2559
02:23:18,358 --> 02:23:21,527
Dean, you said the enemy committed

2560
02:23:21,561 --> 02:23:24,030
175,000 men to the offensive.

2561
02:23:24,064 --> 02:23:25,465
That's right, Clark.

2562
02:23:25,498 --> 02:23:28,401
And General Westmoreland says
that they suffered 45,000 killed,

2563
02:23:28,434 --> 02:23:31,237
with a 1-to-3.5
killed-to-wounded ratio.

2564
02:23:31,271 --> 02:23:33,173
It's right here in my report.

2565
02:23:33,206 --> 02:23:36,042
We beat the pants off them.

2566
02:23:36,076 --> 02:23:38,544
Then how in hell do we justify to the public

2567
02:23:38,578 --> 02:23:40,981
sending hundreds of thousands more men?

2568
02:23:41,014 --> 02:23:42,782
We tell them this.

2569
02:23:42,815 --> 02:23:45,151
That we're within inches of victory.

2570
02:23:45,185 --> 02:23:46,686
Inches.

2571
02:23:46,719 --> 02:23:49,489
45,000 killed, yes, General?

2572
02:23:49,522 --> 02:23:50,924
Yes, sir.

2573
02:23:50,957 --> 02:23:53,293
And three and a half times that
number are out of action?

2574
02:23:53,326 --> 02:23:54,995
It's in the report, Clark.

2575
02:23:55,028 --> 02:23:57,297
If there's 45,000 dead

2576
02:23:57,330 --> 02:23:59,799
and three and a half times that number...

2577
02:23:59,832 --> 02:24:01,367
160,000.

2578
02:24:01,401 --> 02:24:06,907
157,500 wounded, plus 45,000 dead...

2579
02:24:06,940 --> 02:24:11,878
General, according to you
and General Westmoreland,

2580
02:24:11,912 --> 02:24:17,183
we have killed and wounded
120% of the enemy.

2581
02:24:22,788 --> 02:24:25,858
It's becoming more and more evident

2582
02:24:25,892 --> 02:24:28,628
that an out-and-out
military victory

2583
02:24:28,661 --> 02:24:33,066
cannot be achieved with any strategy.

2584
02:24:33,099 --> 02:24:36,469
So, these are my recommendations.

2585
02:24:36,502 --> 02:24:41,374
Send Westmoreland only those forces

2586
02:24:41,407 --> 02:24:44,244
that will satisfy his immediate needs.

2587
02:24:44,277 --> 02:24:46,479
Wheeler has agreed to 22,000

2588
02:24:46,512 --> 02:24:48,581
plus the units previously approved

2589
02:24:48,614 --> 02:24:50,716
and already scheduled for deployment.

2590
02:24:50,750 --> 02:24:53,153
This would stave off immediate defeat

2591
02:24:53,186 --> 02:24:56,022
while we move to negotiations.

2592
02:24:56,056 --> 02:24:59,825
We realize that the settlement
will not be favorable for Saigon,

2593
02:24:59,859 --> 02:25:02,395
and they would fight it.

2594
02:25:02,428 --> 02:25:05,298
The bombing.

2595
02:25:05,331 --> 02:25:08,734
Wheeler, the other chiefs and Walt Rostow

2596
02:25:08,768 --> 02:25:11,804
all advocate hitting the remaining targets

2597
02:25:11,837 --> 02:25:13,339
in Hanoi and Haiphong

2598
02:25:13,373 --> 02:25:15,741
and mining and bombing the harbors.

2599
02:25:15,775 --> 02:25:18,344
With the support of everyone else,

2600
02:25:18,378 --> 02:25:20,680
I recommend a bombing halt.

2601
02:25:20,713 --> 02:25:24,350
I told you, I'm not gonna stop the bombing.

2602
02:25:24,384 --> 02:25:26,219
It keeps the lead out of our boys.

2603
02:25:26,252 --> 02:25:28,388
There's little evidence
to support that, sir,

2604
02:25:28,421 --> 02:25:31,624
and the bombing is going to be
the single greatest issue

2605
02:25:31,657 --> 02:25:33,293
in the presidential campaign.

2606
02:25:33,326 --> 02:25:36,929
The perception is evolving out there

2607
02:25:36,963 --> 02:25:39,732
that Eugene McCarthy is the peace candidate,

2608
02:25:39,765 --> 02:25:42,969
and you are the war candidate.

2609
02:25:43,003 --> 02:25:46,439
If McCarthy has a good
showing in New Hampshire,

2610
02:25:46,472 --> 02:25:48,508
I think Bobby will throw his hat in.

2611
02:25:48,541 --> 02:25:51,444
But he can't beat you if you're
sitting at the peace table.

2612
02:25:51,477 --> 02:25:53,113
Peace table!

2613
02:25:53,146 --> 02:25:54,747
Sell out South Vietnam?

2614
02:25:54,780 --> 02:25:56,616
This is your advice?

2615
02:25:56,649 --> 02:26:00,020
If I could lay a plan
to win the war before...

2616
02:26:00,053 --> 02:26:01,421
I gotta go on TV in three weeks

2617
02:26:01,454 --> 02:26:03,723
and explain all this to the American people!

2618
02:26:03,756 --> 02:26:06,226
And you're telling me to
cut and run, admit defeat.

2619
02:26:06,259 --> 02:26:08,995
That 20,000 American boys
have died for nothing!

2620
02:26:09,029 --> 02:26:11,998
That 20,000 American mothers
weep for nothing!

2621
02:26:12,032 --> 02:26:14,334
The situation has changed since Tet.

2622
02:26:14,367 --> 02:26:16,602
Yes, it has!
Tet was a failure!

2623
02:26:16,636 --> 02:26:18,238
The enemy has failed to overrun us.

2624
02:26:18,271 --> 02:26:20,240
We are poised to win,

2625
02:26:20,273 --> 02:26:21,841
and now it's only you and your people

2626
02:26:21,874 --> 02:26:24,277
who are advising against
the extra effort it'll take

2627
02:26:24,310 --> 02:26:27,513
to turn three years of
miserable war into victory!

2628
02:26:27,547 --> 02:26:31,017
And I'm telling you there is
no victory to be had!

2629
02:26:31,051 --> 02:26:33,986
Not without measures that'll
tear this country apart

2630
02:26:34,020 --> 02:26:35,688
and bring down this administration!

2631
02:26:35,721 --> 02:26:38,491
I told you to get out of Vietnam
three years ago, Lyndon...

2632
02:26:38,524 --> 02:26:40,793
What about two years ago, and one?

2633
02:26:40,826 --> 02:26:42,628
You shot down every bombing pause,

2634
02:26:42,662 --> 02:26:44,197
backed every troop increase!

2635
02:26:44,230 --> 02:26:45,631
Don't you dare!

2636
02:26:45,665 --> 02:26:47,133
Excuse me, Mr. President!

2637
02:26:47,167 --> 02:26:49,635
My counsel has not deviated one whit!

2638
02:26:49,669 --> 02:26:52,738
My every word, then as now,

2639
02:26:52,772 --> 02:26:55,275
has been informed solely by my commitment

2640
02:26:55,308 --> 02:26:57,277
to preserve your presidency

2641
02:26:57,310 --> 02:27:00,113
and establish your place in
this country's history!

2642
02:27:00,146 --> 02:27:02,715
I should have cleaned house November '63.

2643
02:27:02,748 --> 02:27:04,250
Got rid of all of 'em.

2644
02:27:04,284 --> 02:27:06,986
McNamara, Bundy, Connally.

2645
02:27:07,019 --> 02:27:09,822
Warned me those fucking Kennedy lovers

2646
02:27:09,855 --> 02:27:11,624
would be disloyal to me!

2647
02:27:11,657 --> 02:27:13,693
All of 'em!

2648
02:27:21,267 --> 02:27:26,139
They all may have
advised you, Mr. President.

2649
02:27:26,172 --> 02:27:30,042
You decided.

2650
02:27:30,076 --> 02:27:33,246
Against all your natural instincts.

2651
02:27:33,279 --> 02:27:36,682
Against the whole of your life experience.

2652
02:27:38,884 --> 02:27:40,986
You decided.

2653
02:27:45,525 --> 02:27:49,061
Man, on TV: Senator Eugene
McCarthy, a dove on Vietnam,

2654
02:27:49,095 --> 02:27:52,732
who was virtually unknown to voters
of this state two months ago,

2655
02:27:52,765 --> 02:27:54,434
has finished in a virtual tie

2656
02:27:54,467 --> 02:27:56,345
with the sitting President
of the United States,

2657
02:27:56,369 --> 02:27:58,304
Lyndon Johnson.

2658
02:27:58,338 --> 02:28:00,740
Since polls taken only a week ago

2659
02:28:00,773 --> 02:28:03,376
predicted Johnson would win
two-thirds of the vote

2660
02:28:03,409 --> 02:28:05,345
and McCarthy only 11%,

2661
02:28:05,378 --> 02:28:07,380
the senator's surprisingly high turnout

2662
02:28:07,413 --> 02:28:08,948
has shocked the country.

2663
02:28:08,981 --> 02:28:12,452
I run because it is now unmistakably clear

2664
02:28:12,485 --> 02:28:17,457
that we can change these
disastrous, divisive policies

2665
02:28:17,490 --> 02:28:21,561
only by changing the men who
are now making them.

2666
02:28:21,594 --> 02:28:26,031
I run because I am convinced
that this country

2667
02:28:26,065 --> 02:28:28,201
is on a perilous course

2668
02:28:28,234 --> 02:28:32,037
and because I have such strong feelings

2669
02:28:32,071 --> 02:28:34,174
about what must be done,

2670
02:28:34,207 --> 02:28:38,444
and I feel that I am obliged
to do all that I can.

2671
02:28:38,478 --> 02:28:40,580
I was there.

2672
02:28:40,613 --> 02:28:42,758
I was there when you told your
brother to go into that place.

2673
02:28:42,782 --> 02:28:44,150
I was there.

2674
02:28:44,184 --> 02:28:45,818
And now I'm paying for it,

2675
02:28:45,851 --> 02:28:49,989
day after day after day
while you cut me to pieces!

2676
02:28:50,022 --> 02:28:54,660
There's blood on your hands, you traitor!

2677
02:28:54,694 --> 02:28:56,162
Our troops are being killed

2678
02:28:56,196 --> 02:28:59,365
by the bullets and the mines of the south.

2679
02:28:59,399 --> 02:29:01,167
If by ending the bombing of the north

2680
02:29:01,201 --> 02:29:03,369
we can bring peace to South Vietnam,

2681
02:29:03,403 --> 02:29:06,906
then we will save the lives of
thousands of our young men

2682
02:29:06,939 --> 02:29:09,609
and thousands of Vietnamese.

2683
02:29:27,427 --> 02:29:29,529
Yes, Mr. President?

2684
02:29:29,562 --> 02:29:32,131
I talked to Mills.

2685
02:29:32,164 --> 02:29:34,767
He won't back a war surtax

2686
02:29:34,800 --> 02:29:37,837
unless we go on TV and announce deep cuts.

2687
02:29:37,870 --> 02:29:39,605
I want you to go up there

2688
02:29:39,639 --> 02:29:41,741
and talk to everybody at Ways and Means.

2689
02:29:41,774 --> 02:29:43,685
I'm meeting with five of them
in the morning, sir.

2690
02:29:43,709 --> 02:29:46,346
Take Ackley up with you
to back up the numbers.

2691
02:29:46,379 --> 02:29:48,690
They don't believe anything
out of the White House anymore.

2692
02:29:48,714 --> 02:29:50,616
It's a good idea.

2693
02:29:50,650 --> 02:29:51,884
Anything else,
Mr. President?

2694
02:29:51,917 --> 02:29:53,853
I...

2695
02:29:58,057 --> 02:29:59,692
Are you all right,
Mr. President?

2696
02:30:02,395 --> 02:30:05,164
I'm all right, Joe.

2697
02:30:10,470 --> 02:30:12,071
Joe?

2698
02:30:14,707 --> 02:30:18,344
Senator Kennedy's speech,
who wrote it for him?

2699
02:30:21,414 --> 02:30:23,383
This guy Walinsky on his staff's

2700
02:30:23,416 --> 02:30:24,626
been writing a lot of his stuff.

2701
02:30:24,650 --> 02:30:28,388
I don't know.
Maybe Schlesinger, Sorensen.

2702
02:30:28,421 --> 02:30:29,689
Goodwin.

2703
02:30:29,722 --> 02:30:34,760
I think he was involved, yes.

2704
02:30:36,462 --> 02:30:38,364
All right, Joe.
Thanks.

2705
02:30:38,398 --> 02:30:40,433
Yes, sir.

2706
02:30:48,073 --> 02:30:50,410
Dr. King, on TV: I could
never again raise my voice

2707
02:30:50,443 --> 02:30:53,346
against the violence of
the oppressed in the ghettos

2708
02:30:53,379 --> 02:30:55,748
without having spoken first clearly

2709
02:30:55,781 --> 02:30:59,151
to the greatest purveyor
of violence in the world today:

2710
02:30:59,184 --> 02:31:01,387
My own government.

2711
02:31:09,629 --> 02:31:11,931
How many kids did you kill today?

2712
02:31:11,964 --> 02:31:17,370
Hey, hey, LBJ! How many kids
did you kill today?

2713
02:31:17,403 --> 02:31:19,147
Man, on TV: The largest
antiwar demonstration yet

2714
02:31:19,171 --> 02:31:21,140
brought hundreds of thousands of protesters

2715
02:31:21,173 --> 02:31:23,309
into the streets of American cities.

2716
02:31:23,343 --> 02:31:26,679
The radicals say that since peaceful
demonstrations won't end the war,

2717
02:31:26,712 --> 02:31:29,749
they're ready to move
from protest to resistance.

2718
02:31:29,782 --> 02:31:32,785
With talk of full-scale
rebellion sweeping the country

2719
02:31:32,818 --> 02:31:34,854
from college campuses to the inner cities,

2720
02:31:34,887 --> 02:31:36,856
the mood is turning ugly,

2721
02:31:36,889 --> 02:31:38,458
and there's a dangerous sense

2722
02:31:38,491 --> 02:31:40,025
that the nation's political life

2723
02:31:40,059 --> 02:31:41,427
is spinning out of control.

2724
02:31:41,461 --> 02:31:44,063
For it seems now more certain than ever

2725
02:31:44,096 --> 02:31:46,399
that the bloody experience of Vietnam

2726
02:31:46,432 --> 02:31:48,568
is to end in a stalemate.

2727
02:31:48,601 --> 02:31:51,236
This summer's almost certain standoff

2728
02:31:51,270 --> 02:31:54,940
will either end in real
give-and-take negotiations

2729
02:31:54,974 --> 02:31:57,309
or terrible escalation.

2730
02:31:57,343 --> 02:32:00,413
But it is increasingly clear
to this reporter

2731
02:32:00,446 --> 02:32:03,383
that the only rational way out, then,

2732
02:32:03,416 --> 02:32:05,017
will be to negotiate.

2733
02:32:05,050 --> 02:32:08,354
Not as victors, but as an honorable people

2734
02:32:08,388 --> 02:32:11,424
who lived up to their pledge
to defend democracy

2735
02:32:11,457 --> 02:32:14,193
and did the best they could.

2736
02:32:14,226 --> 02:32:16,662
This is Walter Cronkite.
Good night.

2737
02:33:25,465 --> 02:33:28,768
Well, say what you think.

2738
02:33:30,670 --> 02:33:32,905
All right.

2739
02:33:32,938 --> 02:33:34,139
It's tough.

2740
02:33:34,173 --> 02:33:35,775
And effective.

2741
02:33:35,808 --> 02:33:41,447
But the music in it
is sad and sour to the ear.

2742
02:33:41,481 --> 02:33:43,616
And I don't know that any speechwriter

2743
02:33:43,649 --> 02:33:45,718
could have made it sing.

2744
02:33:47,987 --> 02:33:50,590
I got a hundred bills in committee.

2745
02:33:50,623 --> 02:33:53,092
They'll never see the light of day.

2746
02:33:53,125 --> 02:33:55,427
But I think I can pass a thousand bills.

2747
02:33:55,461 --> 02:33:57,296
More education, more health care,

2748
02:33:57,329 --> 02:33:58,864
more rights.

2749
02:33:58,898 --> 02:34:00,900
But it wouldn't matter.

2750
02:34:00,933 --> 02:34:03,268
'Cause it seems nothing I say,
no matter how I say it,

2751
02:34:03,302 --> 02:34:06,639
could ever bring this country
together again.

2752
02:34:08,173 --> 02:34:12,645
Then perhaps eloquence of speech

2753
02:34:12,678 --> 02:34:14,680
is no longer the answer,

2754
02:34:14,714 --> 02:34:16,782
but eloquence of action.

2755
02:34:26,526 --> 02:34:27,993
Mr. Secretary.

2756
02:34:28,027 --> 02:34:29,304
Would you be kind enough to make sure

2757
02:34:29,328 --> 02:34:31,564
that the president sees that this evening?

2758
02:34:31,597 --> 02:34:33,666
- Clark.
- Lady Bird.

2759
02:34:33,699 --> 02:34:37,202
I promised that he'd have those
budget figures by the end of the day.

2760
02:34:37,236 --> 02:34:38,938
He's right inside.

2761
02:34:38,971 --> 02:34:41,741
No, no, I won't disturb him.

2762
02:34:41,774 --> 02:34:43,208
Thank you. Good night.

2763
02:34:43,242 --> 02:34:45,277
Clark.

2764
02:34:46,879 --> 02:34:49,248
Clark, I...

2765
02:34:49,281 --> 02:34:52,151
I got the speech here.

2766
02:34:52,184 --> 02:34:55,821
I need your help with it.

2767
02:34:55,855 --> 02:34:58,624
You know that I'm at your
service, Mr. President.

2768
02:34:58,658 --> 02:35:00,292
I know, old friend.

2769
02:35:58,951 --> 02:36:02,154
Good evening, my fellow Americans.

2770
02:36:02,187 --> 02:36:04,456
Tonight, I want to speak to you

2771
02:36:04,489 --> 02:36:08,661
of peace in Vietnam and Southeast Asia.

2772
02:36:08,694 --> 02:36:11,330
We are prepared to move immediately

2773
02:36:11,363 --> 02:36:14,133
towards peace through negotiations.

2774
02:36:14,166 --> 02:36:17,569
We are reducing, substantially reducing,

2775
02:36:17,603 --> 02:36:19,739
the present level of hostilities,

2776
02:36:19,772 --> 02:36:24,376
and we are doing so unilaterally
and at once.

2777
02:36:24,409 --> 02:36:30,549
Tonight, I have ordered our
aircraft and our naval vessels

2778
02:36:30,582 --> 02:36:34,286
to make no more attacks on North Vietnam

2779
02:36:34,319 --> 02:36:38,357
except in the area north of
the demilitarized zone

2780
02:36:38,390 --> 02:36:40,926
where the continuing enemy buildup

2781
02:36:40,960 --> 02:36:44,664
directly threatens allied forward positions.

2782
02:36:44,697 --> 02:36:48,167
The area in which we are
stopping our attacks

2783
02:36:48,200 --> 02:36:52,805
includes almost 90% of
North Vietnam's population

2784
02:36:52,838 --> 02:36:54,707
and most of its territory.

2785
02:36:54,740 --> 02:36:58,043
Our purpose in this action

2786
02:36:58,077 --> 02:37:00,045
is to bring about a reduction

2787
02:37:00,079 --> 02:37:02,815
in the level of violence that now exists.

2788
02:37:02,848 --> 02:37:06,719
It is to save the lives of brave men

2789
02:37:06,752 --> 02:37:09,789
and to save the lives of
innocent women and children.

2790
02:37:09,822 --> 02:37:13,392
Now, as in the past,

2791
02:37:13,425 --> 02:37:16,929
the United States is ready
to send its representatives

2792
02:37:16,962 --> 02:37:19,932
in any forum at any time

2793
02:37:19,965 --> 02:37:25,938
to discuss the means of bringing
this ugly war to an end.

2794
02:37:25,971 --> 02:37:31,243
There is a division
in the American house now.

2795
02:37:31,276 --> 02:37:34,179
There is divisiveness among us all tonight.

2796
02:37:34,213 --> 02:37:38,283
With America's sons in the fields far away,

2797
02:37:38,317 --> 02:37:42,788
with America's future under
challenge right here at home,

2798
02:37:42,822 --> 02:37:46,325
with our hopes and the world's
hopes for peace

2799
02:37:46,358 --> 02:37:49,061
in the balance every day,

2800
02:37:49,094 --> 02:37:51,463
I do not believe that I should

2801
02:37:51,496 --> 02:37:54,099
devote an hour or a day of my time

2802
02:37:54,133 --> 02:37:57,703
to any personal partisan causes

2803
02:37:57,737 --> 02:38:02,607
or to any duties other than the
awesome duties of this office,

2804
02:38:02,641 --> 02:38:05,544
the presidency of your country.

2805
02:38:07,747 --> 02:38:11,516
Accordingly, I shall not seek,

2806
02:38:11,550 --> 02:38:13,452
and I will not accept,

2807
02:38:13,485 --> 02:38:16,088
the nomination of my party

2808
02:38:16,121 --> 02:38:21,193
for another term as your president.

2809
02:38:24,964 --> 02:38:28,433
But let men everywhere know, however,

2810
02:38:28,467 --> 02:38:31,103
that a strong and a confident

2811
02:38:31,136 --> 02:38:34,439
and a vigilant America stands ready tonight

2812
02:38:34,473 --> 02:38:36,441
to seek an honorable peace

2813
02:38:36,475 --> 02:38:38,577
and stands ready tonight

2814
02:38:38,610 --> 02:38:40,579
to defend an honored cause,

2815
02:38:40,612 --> 02:38:44,016
whatever the price, whatever the burden,

2816
02:38:44,049 --> 02:38:49,321
whatever the sacrifice that
duty may require.

2817
02:38:49,354 --> 02:38:52,324
Thank you for listening.

2818
02:38:52,357 --> 02:38:56,829
Good night, and God bless you all.

